---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

export const prerender = true;

const title = "Observability Contract";
const description = "Advanced two-mode JSON structured logging framework with centralized payload masking, tracing, and metric summarization.";
---

<BaseLayout title={`${title} | Sriman Tirupathy Eshwarappa`} description={description}>
  
  <article class="pt-32 pb-24">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-4xl">
      
      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <a href="/accelerators" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-accent font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-widest hover:text-slate-900 transition-colors mb-8">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="19" y1="12" x2="5" y2="12"></line><polyline points="12 19 5 12 12 5"></polyline></svg>
          Back to Accelerators
        </a>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6 tracking-tighter italic">{title}</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          More than just a custom logger, this component is a strict architectural contract that forces every MuleSoft API in the enterprise to speak the exact same structured JSON dialect. Built with a unique two-mode architecture, it minimizes runtime footprint while enabling rapid root-cause diagnosis.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-8">
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest border border-slate-200">Mule 4</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest border border-slate-200">Observability</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest border border-slate-200">DataWeave Masking</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest border border-slate-200">Splunk / ELK</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <!-- Architecture Metrics -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-16">
        <div class="glass p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">~0%</div>
          <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-500">I/O Blocking</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mt-2">Driven by Log4j2 Asynchronous Appenders.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="glass p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">2 Modes</div>
          <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-500">INFO vs DEBUG</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mt-2">Explicit separation between lean routing and dense diagnostics.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="glass p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">100%</div>
          <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-500">Event Traceability</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mt-2">Universal correlation propagation across the entire API Network.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Core Features -->
      <div class="prose prose-slate prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h2>The Observability Philosophy</h2>
        <p>
          Integrations are the nervous system of an enterprise. But when logs are noisy, unstructured, or missing critical correlation, support teams spend expensive hours "grep-ing" through disparate systems to find the root cause of an outage. Standard <code>logger</code> components allow developers to log <em>anything</em>, which results in chaos.
        </p>

        <p>
          This accelerator solves that by abstracting all logging logic into semantic Mule subflows (e.g., <code>obs-log-outbound-request</code>). This serves three purposes:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Zero Configuration Drift:</strong> Modifying the schema here upgrades logging for 100+ integrations on their next build.</li>
          <li><strong>Deep Masking:</strong> Sensitive PII/PCI fields are recursively truncated before hitting the aggregator.</li>
          <li><strong>Eliminates Boilerplate:</strong> Developers focus entirely on business logic instead of crafting log layouts.</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="my-12 border-slate-200" />

        <h2>Two-Mode Verbosity Architecture</h2>
        <p>The framework prioritizes <strong>"faster diagnosis with fewer logs."</strong></p>

        <h3>1. INFO Mode: The Lean Default</h3>
        <p>
          Active for >99% of production volume. It logs only major milestones like `FLOW_START` and `OUTBOUND_RESPONSE`. Crucially, it replaces entire payloads with a lightweight <code>payloadSummary</code>.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-2xl p-6 my-6 shadow-xl overflow-x-auto relative group">
          <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 px-2 py-1 bg-white/10 rounded text-[10px] font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-widest">INFO Output</div>
          <pre is:raw><code class="language-json text-sm text-slate-300">{
  "timestamp": "2026-03-12T10:15:30.123Z",
  "level": "INFO",
  "eventType": "OUTBOUND_RESPONSE",
  "application": {
    "apiName": "customer-system-api",
    "environment": "prod"
  },
  "trace": { "correlationId": "8b9cad0e..." },
  "targetMetadata": {
    "targetSystem": "SAP ERP",
    "httpStatus": 201
  },
  "payloadSummary": {
    "type": "Object",
    "attributeCount": 5,
    "topLevelKeys": ["sapId", "status"]
  }
}</code></pre>
        </div>

        <h3>2. DEBUG Mode: Targeted Deep Diagnostics</h3>
        <p>
          When an incident occurs and the payload summary isn't enough, architects can dynamically switch the <code>obs.debug.enabled</code> property to <code>true</code>. The framework immediately begins executing deep redaction scans, generating robust <code>diagnostics.before</code> and <code>diagnostics.after</code> snapshots.
        </p>
        
        <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-2xl p-6 my-6 shadow-xl overflow-x-auto relative group">
          <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 px-2 py-1 border border-accent/30 text-accent rounded text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest bg-accent/10">DEBUG Output</div>
          <pre is:raw><code class="language-json text-sm text-slate-300">{
  "level": "DEBUG",
  "eventType": "OUTBOUND_REQUEST",
  "diagnostics": {
    "before": {
      "payload": {
         "customerId": "CUST-88910",
         "name": "Jane Doe",
         "apiSecret": "*** REDACTED ***"
      }
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
        </div>

        <h2>Centralized Security: The Redaction Engine</h2>
        <p>
          Logging sensitive data is a primary vector for compliance breaches. Rather than trusting individual developers to manually strip passwords, this component utilizes a master recursive DataWeave module (<code>masking-rules.dwl</code>). It automatically truncates massive arrays to prevent memory spikes and overwrites fields matching the global zero-trust dictionary (e.g., <code>"password"</code>, <code>"authorization"</code>, <code>"ssn"</code>) with <code>*** REDACTED ***</code> regardless of where they are nested in the payload tree.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-16 p-8 bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-3xl text-center">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 italic">Ready to standardize your enterprise metrics?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8 max-w-lg mx-auto">
            You can inject this reusable Maven abstraction directly into your API specifications to radically improve operational visibility.
          </p>
          <a href="https://github.com/shrimante/mulesoft-observability-contract" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-xl hover:bg-accent transition-all duration-300 shadow-xl hover:shadow-accent/20 font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-xs">
            View Source Code on GitHub
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"></path><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3"></line></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
